> (without the additional check to reject pointers, as we would need GNU C for that, see e.g. [stackoverflow.com/a/19455169](https://stackoverflow.com/a/19455169);

GNU C is not an issue if we sandwich it in a `#if SECP256K1_GNUC_PREREQ`. A check that works only on GCC will be enough for us; we'll always test on GCC.

And we don't need `BUILD_BUG_ON_ZERO` because we have a similar `STATIC_ASSERT` macro. (Though I really like the [implementation of `BUILD_BUG_ON_ZERO`](https://github.com/torvalds/linux/blob/6f0d349d922ba44e4348a17a78ea51b7135965b1/tools/include/linux/bug.h) and that it is an expression and not a statement; our macro is a statement that cannot be used anywhere `BUILD_BUG_ON_ZERO` can be used.)
